        SpecifySpecConst:
          Variable: true
        Title:
          String: Mesh Type
        Title0:
          String: Quad
        Title1:
          String: 3D Mesh
        Tooltip:
          String: "Determines how the particle positions and normals will be calculated.\\n\\nQuad = the default particle setting. Used to render 2D particles that face the camera. Useful for effects that only need textures (like sparkles and snow). When using this mode, ensure that Double-Sided rendering is enabled. In most cases, Depth Write can be disabled.\\n\\n3D Mesh = 3D particles that can move and rotate independently in 3D space. Useful for rendering full 3D objects that benefit from complex rotation and lighting (like asteroids and crowds). When using this mode, make sure that Double-Sided rendering is disabled and Depth Write is enabled. Note that this mode is more computationally expensive."
      PositionX: -3679
      PositionY: -1660
      TemplateID: nodes_inputs_parameters_droplist
      Title1: DropList Parameter
      Title2: Mesh Type
